<title>Remarks concerning copies of Bushman pictures nos. I-XXIV Collected By Mr H.C. Schunke, and deposited in the Grey Library</title>
<summary><i>Explanatory remarks concerning copies of Bushmen Paintings and Etchings, collected by Mr. H.C. Schunke and deposited in the Grey Library.  Partly in Bushman by and partly in English after |han≠kass&apos;o (L VIII.-1. 6054-6057, 6061-6073).</i> A list of remarks by |han≠kass&apos;o alongside the numbers (I-XXIV) of a collection of copies of paintings found in the Grey Library. These paintings are mostly of animals and rainmakers and their work with the rain.</summary><comments>1) p.6067v &amp; 6068v: |han≠kass&apos;o&apos;s note on &apos;another <i>!khoa ka ||kerri-ssi !kau&apos;</i>; a note on the <i>!khoa ka ||kerri-ssi !kau</i> that |han≠kass&apos;o saw in a painting copied by a &apos;Kafir&apos; artist, 2) p.6071v: on a man called <i>Oud Koos,</i> or <i>!ka !kain-i</i>, 3) See also <i>An account of the rain&apos;s things or &apos;!khoa ka ||kerri-ssi !kau&apos;</i>, 4) This story is found in Book VIII-1</comments><date>12 January 1878 (started)</date><storypages>6054-6057, 6061-6073</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><category>The Rain and Rain&apos;s water</category><author>|han≠kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>Grey Library</kw><subkw>Mr H.C. Schunke copies of rock paintings at</subkw></keyword>
